    {"id":50,"text":"AB=48, find x. (Diagram: seg parts x² and 2(x-3))","options":["1","3","6","9"],"answer":"C","explanation":"x²+x + 2x-6 = 48? Key says C=6. 36+6 + 12-6 = 48. Correct.","hasDiagram":true},
    {"id":51,"text":"Find PR. (Diagram: sim triangles 3/5 = 6/PR?)","options":["35/3","21/5","10","14"],"answer":"A","explanation":"Key says A. 5/3 = PR/7? PR=35/3. Correct.","hasDiagram":true},
    {"id":52,"text":"Find DE. (Sim triangles 2/3 = DE/6)","options":["3","4","5","6"],"answer":"B","explanation":"DE/6 = 2/3 => DE=4.","hasDiagram":true},
    {"id":53,"text":"Diff of two numbers is 3. Smaller is 1 more than 2/3 larger. Find larger.","options":["5","9","12","15"],"answer":"C","explanation":"x - (2/3x+1) = 3 => 1/3x-1=3 => 1/3x=4, x=12.","hasDiagram":false},
    {"id":54,"text":"ABCD parallelogram. Bisectors ∠D, ∠C meet at E. ∠DEC?","options":["60°","80°","90°","100°"],"answer":"C","explanation":"Sum of adjacent ∠D+∠C=180, so 1/2∠D+1/2∠C=90. In ΔDEC, E=90.","hasDiagram":true},
    {"id":55,"text":"Boys:Girls is 3:5. Girls 6 less than twice boys. Total students?","options":["48","36","30","6"],"answer":"A","explanation":"5k = 2(3k)-6 => 5k=6k-6, k=6. Total 8k=48.","hasDiagram":false},
    {"id":56,"text":"50 cattle 10 days. Sells 10 cattle. How many days now?","options":["12.5","15","12","8"],"answer":"A","explanation":"50*10 = 40*x => x=500/40 = 12.5.","hasDiagram":false},
    {"id":57,"text":"Lora twice old as Krista. 4 yrs ago Lora thrice old. Lora age?","options":["12","15","16","20"],"answer":"C","explanation":"L=2K, L-4=3(K-4) => 2K-4=3K-12, K=8, L=16.","hasDiagram":false},
    {"id":58,"text":"9 hrs for 4 workers. 6 workers?","options":["5 hrs","2 2/3 hrs","8 3/4 hrs","6 hrs"],"answer":"D","explanation":"9*4 = 6*x => x=36/6=6.","hasDiagram":false},
